<subSubSection id="D48C652EFFC6FF81FA0B979AFD43FDAE" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="316" pageId="10" pageNumber="315" type="description">
<paragraph id="9C2936A5FFC6FF81FA0B979AFD43FDAE" blockId="10.[1426,2628,3167,3274]" lastBlockId="11.[186,1391,296,1151]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="316" pageId="10" pageNumber="315">
<emphasis id="AEE2EAB7FFC6FF80FA0B979AF912F304" bold="true" box="[1426,1678,3206,3235]" pageId="10" pageNumber="315">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 33.5-35. 
<quantity id="5B6E9B40FFC6FF80F820979AF79DF304" box="[1977,2049,3206,3235]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="315" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
(males), 31-33 cm (females), tail 32.5-36. 
<quantity id="5B6E9B40FFC6FF80FA2497B1F99AF36D" box="[1469,1542,3245,3274]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="315" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
(males), 34-34. 
<quantity id="5B6E9B40FFC6FF80F96D97B1F8A2F36D" box="[1780,1854,3245,3274]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="315" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
(females), hindfoot 6.9-7. 
<quantity id="5B6E9B40FFC6FF80F75E97B1F68EF36D" box="[2247,2322,3245,3274]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="315" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
(males), 6.4-6. 
<quantity id="5B6E9B40FFC6FF80F66097B1F5DFF36D" box="[2553,2627,3245,3274]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="315" unit="cm" value="6.0">6 cm</quantity>
females, ear 2:7.2-8 cm (males), 2.4-2. 
<quantity id="5B6E9B40FFC7FF81FD689A34FCABFEE2" box="[753,823,296,325]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="316" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
(females); weight similar to that of the Common Slender Mongoose. A small mongoose, with a long slender body and long tail (equal to body length). Variable body and tail color, generally either reddish (from chestnut to yellow; 
<emphasis id="AEE2EAB7FFC7FF81FE5E9A85FDD6FE1D" box="[455,586,409,442]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">shortridgei</emphasis>
) or dark brown to black (
<emphasis id="AEE2EAB7FFC7FF81FC369A85FB88FE1D" box="[943,1044,409,442]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">nigrata</emphasis>
). Skull length 63-68 mm (males larger than females). Skull larger than the Common Slender Mongoose and smaller than the 
<collectingRegion id="5E52F847FFC7FF81FE329AF0FE6DFDAE" box="[427,497,492,521]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">Cape</collectingRegion>
Gray Mongoose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="C8E9662DFFC6FF80FF05963BFD96F236" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6347113" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6347113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6347113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="315" startId="10.[156,186,3367,3392]" targetBox="[12,2797,17,3639]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="9C2936A5FFC6FF80FF05963BFD96F236" blockId="10.[154,2566,3367,3476]" pageId="10" pageNumber="315">
On following pages: 15. Somalian Slender Mongoose (
<taxonomicName id="5B964D26FFC6FF80FD6A963BFC20F2E7" baseAuthorityName="J. E. Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[755,956,3367,3392]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Bolbitiaceae" genus="Galerella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="315" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ochracea">Galerella ochracea</taxonomicName>
); 16. 
<collectingRegion id="5E52F847FFC6FF80FC62963BFBADF2E7" box="[1019,1073,3367,3392]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="10" pageNumber="315">Cape</collectingRegion>
Gray Mongoose (
<taxonomicName id="5B964D26FFC6FF80FB61963BFA79F2E7" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1272,1509,3367,3392]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Bolbitiaceae" genus="Galerella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="316" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pulverulenta">
